1. Build a container image using Podman with name my-app:1.0 using /root/app-source as build context
2. Save the image as a tarball to /root/my-app.tar

# The following exercise creates an image (based on ngixin ) to understand build and save command
mkdir ckad-nginx
echo "<h1>Hello from my custom Podman Image!</h1>" > index.html

vi Containerfile
# Use the official production-ready Nginx base image
FROM docker.io/library/nginx:alpine

# Copy your custom webpage into the server's default public directory
COPY index.html /usr/share/nginx/html/index.html

# Expose port 80 to allow incoming network traffic
EXPOSE 80

## Build the image - CRITICAL commands
podman build -t ckadnginx:v1 .
podman images

